         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Sunday, 30 May 1886. ¶  ¶ Today, dear Mr Holtze, I have completed the description of the  ¶ Eugenia holtzei ¶  and hope to be able to send it to you  ¶ in print ¶  in a week. It is the tree No. 44 ¶  ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">86.05.30</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Maurice Holtze</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">GRG 19/391, Public Library, Museum and Art Gallery, State Records of South Australia, Adelaide.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">Sonntag,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">30/5/86</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Heute, lieber Herr Holtze, habe ich die Beschreibung der Eugenia Holtzei ausgearbeitet, u. hoffe ich Ihnen die Beschreibung in einer Woche </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">gedruckt</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> senden zu können. Es ist der Baum N.44 mit <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name> ähnlichen Blüthen (Kelch).</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich kann aber </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nicht</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> zur Überzeugung kommen dass die Sämlings- oder Keimpflanzen, welche Sie sandten, zum </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">selben</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Baum gehören; daher bitte ich Sie, in nächster Jahreszeit nochmals nach dem Erlang reifer Früchte zu streben, die noch an den jungen beblätterten Zweigen haften.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es ist überhaupt immer gut, beim Sammeln der Herbarium-Exemplare, die in Blüthe sind, </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">jedesmal</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> nach wenigstens </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">jungen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Früchten zu suchen; oft findet man auch noch Frucht Überreste vom vergangenen Jahr. Es spart </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">viel</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Zeit für mich und verhütet Versehen in Benennungen.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sunday, 30 May 1886.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>Today, dear Mr Holtze, I have completed the description of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Eugenia%20holtzei">Eugenia holtzei</name>
               </seg> and hope to be able to send it to you <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">in print</hi>
               </seg> in a week. It is the tree No. 44<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to M. Holtze, 20 February 1886, and M to M. Holtze, 21 March 1886. M described this species in B86.06.01, p.199.</p>
               </note> with the flowers (calyx) similar to <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
               </seg>. However, I am <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> convinced that the juvenile plants or seedlings you sent belong to the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">same</hi>
               </seg> tree. Therefore I ask you to attempt once more in the next season to obtain ripe fruit still attached to the young leaf-bearing branches.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Generally, it is always a good idea when collecting herbarium specimens in flower, to search <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">each time</hi>
               </seg> at least for <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">immature</hi>
               </seg> fruit; often one can also still find remnants of fruit from the previous year. It saves me <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">much</hi>
               </seg> time and prevents mistakes in identifications.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eucalyptus">Eucalyptus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Eugenia%20holtzei">Eugenia holtzei</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
